insects or small animals that are harmful or damaged crops.

44
00:02:44,959 --> 00:02:49,599
Even better, bats appetite for these annoying insects is voracious,

45
00:02:49,599 --> 00:02:51,199
very strong and eager.

46
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:55,359
So far, so good in the friendship between humans and bats.

47
00:02:55,359 --> 00:02:58,159
But then along came the coronavirus pandemic.

48
00:02:58,159 --> 00:03:02,479
And with it, newspaper reports that bats might be to blame.

49
00:03:02,479 --> 00:03:05,759
Before we get into this, we need to explain some terms.

50
00:03:05,759 --> 00:03:09,199
The COVID which people around the world have been suffering from

51
00:03:09,199 --> 00:03:11,439
is the outbreak virus.

52
00:03:11,439 --> 00:03:16,639
But if you go backwards, there's an intermediary known as the progenitor virus.

53
00:03:16,639 --> 00:03:22,239
Between this and the ancestral virus, which is decades or centuries older.

54
00:03:22,239 --> 00:03:28,959
99% of scientists would agree that the ancestral virus of COVID-19 came from bats.

55
00:03:28,959 --> 00:03:34,159
But it's the go between progenitor virus that everyone is searching for now.

56
00:03:34,159 --> 00:03:39,839
One of the scientists leading this search is Lin Fa Wang, a professor at Duke Medical School,

57
00:03:39,839 --> 00:03:41,839
who is known as the Batman of Singapore.

58
